          <p><strong>My Experience:</strong> My timid rescue quickly understood SpotOn's warning tones, rarely needing correction. My neighbor's stubborn dog responded well to Halo's positive reinforcement. <strong>Both systems can work, but SpotOn's wider correction range gives more flexibility.</strong></p>
          <img src="https://betterthanafence.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Collie-Looking-At-Owner-Resize-1024x682.jpg" alt="Border Collie looking at owner near GPS fence boundary" width="1024" height="682" loading="lazy" decoding="async" />
